---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CTAButton from "../components/CTAButton.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Young Rider Course — TT Motorcycle School"
  description="Starting out for the first time? Our Young Rider course is designed for 16+ year olds with no road experience. Theory, hazard perception and off-road scooter training in Sussex."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Young Rider Course</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">Starting Out for the First Time?</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__sub">
        A two-hour introduction designed for 16+ year olds with no road
        experience — theory, hazard perception, and hands-on scooter training in
        a safe, off-road environment.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-grid">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>The Young Rider Course</h2>
        <p>
          For 16+ year olds who have no experience of being on the road, we
          offer a <strong>two-hour lesson</strong>. The first hour is spent at
          our training school where you will practise your theory test questions
          and hazard perception training. The second hour is spent in the safety
          of our secure off-road training area, learning how to control a 50cc
          automatic scooter.
        </p>
        <p>
          This course is ideal for making sure your son or daughter gets the
          best possible start before moving on to Compulsory Basic Training
          (CBT).
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Please note:</strong> we only have automatic 50cc mopeds (no manual
          clutch and gears) for this course.
        </p>

        <h2>For 17+ Riders: New Rider Course</h2>
        <p>
          For riders aged 17 and upwards who have never ridden an automatic or a
          manual bike before (with clutch &amp; gears), our{" "}
          <a href="/new-rider/">New Rider course</a> will give you the skills and
          confidence to move on to your CBT with ease.
        </p>
        <p>
          You will receive personal one-to-one tuition in the safety of our
          secure off-road training area, covering:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pulling away and stopping smoothly</li>
          <li>Changing gears on a manual bike</li>
          <li>
            Slow control techniques — including figure-of-eights and U-turns
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>A Note on Training Duration</h2>
        <p>
          All training course lengths are determined by the individual's level
          of skill and competence. The number of sessions required is advised by
          our instructors following an assessment of your riding skills. This
          assessment is carried out when the CBT road ride (Module E) is
          undertaken.
        </p>

        <h2>What Comes Next?</h2>
        <p>
          After completing the Young Rider course, the natural next step is your <a
            href="/cbt/">CBT (Compulsory Basic Training)</a
          > — the legal requirement to ride on UK roads. From there, you can work
          towards your <a href="/full-licence/">full motorcycle licence</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar__card">
          <h3 class="sidebar__title">Ready to Book?</h3>
          <p class="sidebar__body">
            Young Rider sessions are one-to-one and popular. Secure your spot
            today.
          </p>
          <CTAButton
            href="/cbtbooking/"
            label="Book Your Session"
            variant="accent"
            size="md"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="sidebar__card sidebar__card--plain">
          <h3 class="sidebar__title">Useful Links</h3>
          <ul class="sidebar__links">
            <li><a href="/new-rider/">New Rider Course (17+)</a></li>
            <li><a href="/cbt/">About CBT</a></li>
            <li><a href="/full-licence/">Full Licence Courses</a></li>
            <li><a href="/what-to-wear/">What to Wear</a></li>
            <li><a href="/prices/">View Prices</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contact/">Ask a Question</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .content-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .content-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 300px;
      align-items: start;
    }
  }

  .sidebar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .sidebar__card {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-white);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--space-6);
  }

  .sidebar__card--plain {
    background: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .sidebar__title {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .sidebar__body {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: #ccc;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .sidebar__card--plain .sidebar__body {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .sidebar__links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .sidebar__links a {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .sidebar__links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }
</style>
